t ($15), while trading some reasoning headroom (91 vs 95). Against Gemini 3.1 Pro, Sonnet wins on coding and writing but costs more. The honest assessment: Sonnet 4.6 is the model you should default to unless you have a specific reason to reach for something else.\n\n**When to pick something else:** When the task genuinely requires the last 5% of capability -- complex multi-file refactors, intricate reasoning chains -- upgrade to Opus 4.6. For high-volume, cost-sensitive workloads where quality can flex a bit, Haiku 4.5 at $1/$5 or Gemini 3 Flash at $0.50/$3.00 will save you serious money.","content_length":3213,"generated_at":"2026-05-01"}